snippet.textDisplay:
I’m addict to opioids too.
Not by choice.
I have a terminal illness & the pain has caused seizures & a few heart attacks. I resisted opioids for years until I had no choice if I wanted to stay alive long enough to get my affairs in order & spend some time with my closest loved ones (I have no family).
I am still refusing to increase the dosage any more or to take the Fentanyl patches (yet) bc I know in my gut that it would/will kill me. I know that at some point - I will die from an overdose, either accidental or not.
It sucks when there’s nothing left to do but stay high waiting to die.

snippet.textDisplay:
I haven’t been able to stop listening to this song. This touches my soul in such a painful, but healing way. The love of my life died before we ever got to be together. We were so close but just didn’t get there. Shortly followed by my first friend. We met when we were toddlers and grew up together and our sons are best friends. I have not been able to reconcile with their deaths. I just can’t get over it. This song feels like the friend who doesn’t try to convince you everything will okay, but instead tells you they understand, and holds you through your hurting. This isn’t the first time Grimes has given me healing music, and I love her for it every time. ArtAngels pulled me through rough time too.

Grimes, you are a genius. ❤️

snippet.textDisplay:
On The Side

Sitting in my carriage during another lonely twilight.
Sundown in this inner cold and ugly town.
The edge of forests, scaring away my inner courage with no escape. I'll pull through after a short break.
Down!
The clouds like shrouds of shame guilting me into a harsh plot of horrid dreams.
Waking up in my carriage again.
Another day of lonliness, searching for those forever friends whom don't exist.
Nothing last that long, temporary feelings of contentment are bliss.
Sitting in a wandering carriage, looking for family and and place to rest.
A plot of dirt to grow cabbage and pumpkins in.
Finding out what's important in a friend.
Sitting in my carriage on a dawns sunbeams end looking out over the horizon.
Lonliness in adventure and twist.
Contentment and short lived bliss.
